Specifically, the dynamic weighted-round-robin (WRR) load-balancing
scoring logic in pkg/balancer/wrr — notably the score formula
"sqrt(cs * ss^2 * 1e9 / (lag * cpu))" together with its cold-start
clamps and the nginx-style smooth-WRR picker — is adapted from
go-kratos' warden/selector WRR implementation. The surrounding code
(rolling window, observability surface, gRPC base-balancer integration
and tests) is an independent implementation.

The remainder of this project is an independent reimplementation written
after studying public material only (go-kratos documentation and source,
the gRPC-Go official examples, Google Dapper / SRE publications, and the
Netflix Eureka documentation). It contains no code copied from any
non-public or unlicensed source.
